{"parentUuid":"909f6ee5-be7e-4cdd-9809-56004a9fd188","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"dff115e1-0da9-4646-95d5-cee2397abbd5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TbyF529ZAJ6mp76t3iPcQ5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Downstream Wiring for Cloud Agent v2 Data\n2\t\n3\tThe v2 scheduled agent emits new tagged content (per-position 1h-RV, single-name IV, 25d-RR, MOVE, CDX HY, BTC/ETH order imbalance, vol-band-violation POSITION-ALERTs). These edits make sure local skills actually consume that data rather than letting it sit in Slack.\n4\t\n5\t## Changes applied\n6\t\n7\t| Skill | Edit | Purpose |\n8\t|---|---|---|\n9\t| **positions-monitor** | Added read of `{today}/slack-digest-{today}.md` + auto-invoke `/slack-ingest` if missing | Cloud alerts fire while machine off; must surface next time monitor runs |\n10\t| **positions-monitor** | Added **F12 vol_band** (HIGH) — cloud flagged methodology stop tightened below 1h-RV band | Direct counterpart to v2 cloud agent's vol-band check; cites ABDL 2001 / BPV 2016 Grade A |\n11\t| **positions-monitor** | Added **F13 cloud_alert** (MED) — catchall for any other `[POSITION-ALERT]` not covered by F1–F12 | Prevents cloud intelligence from being silently dropped |\n12\t| **positions-monitor** | Workflow Step 2 now parses digest alerts, matches by ticker. Output cites digest timestamps for F12/F13 lineage | Audit trail back to cloud agent fire |\n13\t| **daily-trade-rec** | Added **Pre-Entry Checklist item 7 — Cloud digest clearance** | Blocks new entries in correlated sleeve if an open position has unresolved vol-band-violation or thesis-breach alert |\n14\t| **market-brief** | Step 4 \"Digest cross-check\" paragraph | When digest has recent `[REGIME]` readings, cross-validate against this step's own pull; discrepancies >1σ flag staleness on one side |\n15\t\n16\t## What was intentionally NOT changed\n17\t\n18\t- **slack-ingest**: already preserves full message text under tagged sections — the new v2 data (per-position vol, MOVE, CDX HY) flows through automatically as markdown text. No parsing logic needed.\n19\t- **trade-update**: one-way push only (Layer 5). Doesn't consume scheduled-agent output.\n20\t- **framework/Memory.md, Methodology Prompt, Data Sources**: unchanged — no new variables, only refresh-frequency changes.\n21\t- **master-data-log.xlsx**: intraday regime readings are NOT persisted to any new sheet. DailyVariables remains the daily EOD log. (If you later want a SlackIntradayLog sheet, that's a new audit step — not required for the decision loop.)\n22\t\n23\t## Dataflow summary\n24\t\n25\t```\n26\t[Cloud scheduled agent fires 08:03/12:07/16:04/00:06 UTC+8]\n27\t           ↓\n28\t    Posts tagged sections to #trading-scheduled-updates\n29\t           ↓\n30\t  [POSITION-STATE]           [REGIME] [NEWS] [THESIS] [POSITION-ALERT]\n31\t           ↑                              ↓\n32\t   trade-update Layer 5             slack-ingest (Step 0 of morning pipeline)\n33\t   pushes on every trade event             ↓\n34\t                              {today}/slack-digest-{today}.md\n35\t                                           ↓\n36\t                         ┌─────────────────┼─────────────────┐\n37\t                         ↓                 ↓                 ↓\n38\t                  market-brief       daily-trade-rec    positions-monitor\n39\t                  (Step 4 cross-     (Step 5 checklist   (F12/F13 flags;\n40\t                   check regime)      item 7)            auto-ingests if\n41\t                                                         digest missing)\n42\t```\n43\t\n44\t## Data coverage check\n45\t\n46\t| v2 cloud output | Consumed by | Status |\n47\t|---|---|---|\n48\t| `[REGIME]` with VIX/MOVE/DXY/US10Y/CDX-HY/SPY | market-brief Step 4 | ✅ cross-check rule added |\n49\t| `[REGIME]` per-position vol (1h-RV, IV, 25d-RR) | positions-monitor F12; daily-trade-rec item 7 | ✅ F12 + checklist |\n50\t| `[NEWS]` bullets | market-brief Step 1 read; trade-rec Step 2 upstream synthesis | ✅ existing digest read |\n51\t| `[THESIS]` per-position deltas | positions-monitor F13; daily-trade-rec item 7 | ✅ F13 + checklist |\n52\t| `[POSITION-ALERT]` any flag | positions-monitor F12/F13 | ✅ |\n53\t| `[POSITION-ALERT]` vol-band-violation specifically | positions-monitor F12 (HIGH) | ✅ dedicated flag |\n54\t\n55\tNothing the cloud agent produces is now silently dropped by local skills.\n56\t\n57\t## Updated skill bundles\n58\t\n59\tAll `.skill` files in `dist-skills/` have been regenerated with these edits:\n60\t\n61\t- `slack-ingest.skill`\n62\t- `trade-update.skill`\n63\t- `market-brief.skill`\n64\t- `daily-trade-rec.skill`\n65\t- `positions-monitor.skill` **(new in this pass)**\n66\t\n67\t## Cowork install — additional prompt\n68\t\n69\tAdd this to `COWORK-PROMPTS.md` (or run it standalone after the first four):\n70\t\n71\t```\n72\t/skill-creator\n73\t\n74\tUpdate the existing `positions-monitor` skill: add slack-digest ingest to the read list, add two new flags (F12 vol_band HIGH, F13 cloud_alert MED) tied to cloud scheduled-agent POSITION-ALERTs, and update workflow to parse digest alerts in Step 2.\n75\t\n76\tSkill configuration:\n77\t- name: positions-monitor\n78\t- model: sonnet\n79\t- allowed-tools: Bash(python3 *) Read Write Edit WebSearch Grep Glob\n80\t- description: \"Intraday watchdog — stop buffer, time-invalidation, earnings, catalyst, thesis variables, portfolio heat, correlation gate. Silent-when-OK. Use for 'check positions', 'monitor book', 'are my stops OK', 'portfolio heat', 'anything flashing'.\"\n81\t\n82\tRequired changes relative to base:\n83\t\n84\t**MODIFY Reads section** — add as item 4:\n85\t4. `{today}/slack-digest-{today}.md` if present (cloud scheduled-agent POSITION-ALERTs, THESIS breaches, vol-band-violation flags). Invoke `/slack-ingest` if digest missing — the cloud agent fires 4x/day while local machine may be off, and its alerts must propagate into local flag panel.\n8